    <h1>Mac Setup</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p><strong style=3D"text-align: left;"><span style=3D"color: rgb(25=
5,0,0);">Caution</span>:</strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(17,17,17);"><spa=
n> If you encounter any system level issue, such as VPN or missing app in s=
elf-service, please contact IT support for assistance by search "IT Help - =
KODI" through the OBI page(<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://intra=
net.westpacgroup.com.au/wib/home" rel=3D"nofollow">https://intranet.westpac=
group.com.au/wib/home</a>).</span></span></p>
<h2 id=3D"MacSetup-FollowthePreSetupsectionsfromMESHMacOSSetup">Follow the =
<strong>Pre Setup </strong>sections from <a href=3D"/display/MD/Mac+OS+Setu=
p">MESH Mac OS Setup</a></h2>
<h2 id=3D"MacSetup-Postman">Postman</h2>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Download Postman (old version) fro=
m here<span> <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/=
Install+Postman" rel=3D"nofollow">Install Postman - Westpac Mesh - Westpac =
Enterprise Confluence</a> (Add in to User folder/Applications folder/ )</sp=
an></span></p>
<h2 id=3D"MacSetup-Homebrew">Homebrew</h2>
<p>Set up Homebrew access token before proceeding to MESH Mac OS Setup: <a =
href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Homebrew" rel=3D=
"nofollow">Homebrew</a></p>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);">Getting 401s? You need an access =
token for Artifactory to use Homebrew in Westpac. Jump to&nbsp;</span><a hr=
ef=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Homebrew#Homebrew-=
AccessToken" rel=3D"nofollow">Configuring Access Token</a></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"MacSetup-VSCode">VS Code</h2>
<p>Enable code command in PATH</p>
<p style=3D"text-align: left;">Add to your ~/.zshrc file</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable" style=3D"text-align: left;">
<tbody class=3D"" style=3D"text-align: left;">
