2. Setting up my environment &amp; tools - Westpac Mesh - Westpac Enterpris=
e Confluence</a></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"MacSetup-SetupProject"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Setu=
p Project&nbsp;</span></h2>
<p>Once all the tools above are setup successfully, refer to this page to u=
nderstand the project architecture and repos/components used:</p>
<p><a href=3D"/display/ARTC/Technical+Design+-+W1C+Channels+UI">Technical D=
esign - W1C Channels UI</a></p>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"MacSetup-FAQ:"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">FAQ:</span><=
/h2>
<p><strong>1.&nbsp;How to connect the macbook to the monitor in the office<=
/strong></p>
<p>Install and open the "DisplayLink Manager" from "Self Service"</p>
<p><strong>2. How to install Node.js v20 if nvm can't fetch the node list?<=
/strong><br>
 If running brew update, brew upgrade, or nvm ls-remote fails, you may need=
 to temporarily point your https_proxy to zScaler instead of the default pr=
oxy. Update your .bash_profile or .zshrc as follows:</p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(106,153,85);"># httpProxyServer=3D<a href=3D"h=
ttp://df.proxy.prod.mte.westpac.com.au:8080" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D=
"nofollow">http://df.proxy.prod.mte.westpac.com.au:8080</a></span><br><span=
 style=3D"color: rgb(106,153,85);"># httpsProxyServer=3D<a href=3D"http://d=
f.proxy.prod.mte.westpac.com.au:8080" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofoll=
ow">http://df.proxy.prod.mte.westpac.com.au:8080</a></span><br><span style=
=3D"color: rgb(156,220,254);">httpsProxyServer</span><span style=3D"color: =
rgb(212,212,212);">=3D</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(206,145,120);"><a hr=
ef=3D"http://127.0.0.1:9000" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">http:=
//127.0.0.1:9000</a></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">This change allows both brew and n=
vm to access the internet (avoiding connection errors). Once nvm can fetch =
external Node.js versions, you can install and use them as usual with nvm u=
se x.x.x.</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);">After successfully installing Node.=
js, make sure to revert the https_proxy value back to its original setting.=
</span></p>
<h2 id=3D"MacSetup-KnownIssue:">Known Issue:</h2>
<p>1. <span style=3D"color: rgb(17,17,17);">MacBooks have issues accessing =
local ports 300X and 800X, which are used by Galaxy SPA and mock servers. U=
sers need to log off the VPN service to run<span> `</span></span><code>npm =
run start`</code><span style=3D"color: rgb(17,17,17);"><span>&nbsp;</span>b=
efore logging back into the VPN.</span></p>
